.TH "provide_user_output" 9 "provide_user_output" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
provide_user_output \- provide output to the user reading a debugfs file.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" provide_user_output
.BI "(int val "  ","
.BI "char __user *u "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ","
.BI "loff_t *ppos "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "val" 12
boolean value for the answer
.IP "u" 12
the buffer to store the answer at
.IP "count" 12
size of the buffer
.IP "ppos" 12
position in the \fIu\fP output buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a simple helper function which stores \fIval\fP boolean value in the user
buffer when the user reads one of UBIFS debugfs files. Returns amount of
bytes written to \fIu\fP in case of success and a negative error code in case of
failure.
